    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2003 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six power plant. This naturally aspirated mill utilizes six individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing to reach its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M-differential lock. Technical highlights include a reinforced rear subframe, refreshed rod bearings, and a cooling system overhauled with an aluminum radiator. The suspension geometry is preserved with Bilstein B6 dampers and fresh control arm bushings, maintaining the sharp turn-in characteristic of the chassis. The exterior is in commendable shape, showing only minor stone chips, while the interior features well-preserved Nappa leather. This is a mechanically sorted example of an iconic driver\u2019s machine.",
